# Backend Standards

## API Design
- Use RESTful conventions for CRUD endpoints
- Return consistent error response format: {"error": str, "code": str, "detail": any}
- Include request_id in all responses for tracing
- Validate all input with Pydantic models

## Lambda Patterns
- Keep handler functions thin — delegate to service layer
- Use structured logging (JSON format)
- Read config from Secrets Manager via pointer pattern
- Cold start budget: <2s for API handlers

## Error Handling
- Map domain exceptions to HTTP status codes
- Never expose internal error details to clients
- Log full stack traces server-side
- Return 5xx for unexpected errors, 4xx for client errors

## Authentication
- Validate JWT tokens from Cognito (when enabled)
- Use middleware for auth, not per-handler logic
- Never trust client-provided user IDs — extract from token
